{"questionId":"22021","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In a small village there are two doctors’ clinics, one owned by Doctor Black and the other&nbsp;owned by Doctor Green. It was noted after each year that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of Doctor Black’s patients&nbsp;moved to Doctor Green’s clinic and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of Doctor Green’s patients moved to Doctor Black’s&nbsp;clinic. All additional losses and gains of patients by the clinics may be ignored.</p>\n<p>At the start of a particular year, it was noted that Doctor Black had <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2100</mn></math> patients on&nbsp;their register, compared to Doctor Green’s <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3500</mn></math> patients.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find a prediction for the ratio of the number of patients Doctor Black will have,&nbsp;compared to Doctor Green, after two years.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>965</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>035</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>95</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2100</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3500</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2294</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3306</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>so ratio is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2294</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>3306</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>1147</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1653</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>693889</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22021","referenceCode":"21M.2.AHL.TZ2.4b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find a prediction for the ratio of the number of patients Doctor Black will have, compared to Doctor Green, after two years.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Eigenvalues and eigenvectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}